	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				No youre right... due to the timing of my posts, i somehow missed this one. However, my point still stands.<BR>
<BR>
The coding involved in a dynamic pet resitance is infathomable, and based on the information available, it seems that there are drawbacks to this new system.<BR>
<BR>
My point is simply that the innate resists of certain pets are being taken away. There are good and bad points to every class and their abilities. I hate to see one of the GOOD things about ANY given class taken away in the interest of balancing, underestimating player creativity, or anything else.<BR>
<BR>
For other pet classes this seems feasable, but not for mages where the innate resits are part of the reason a player uses a certain pet.<BR>
<BR>
I could (and will) go on to talk about the roleplaying issue of this matter. It seems somewhat rediculous to think that a summoned elemental, MADE of fire could be damaged by fire. <BR>
<BR>
Now I am not an expert on the mage pets, else I might be able to argue this point more fully (and I DO intend to research this now), but at least for mages, this seems totally ludicrous.<BR>
<BR>
I hope the dev team takes these points into account regardless of public approval as they truly affect the integrity of the game.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
